definition: superior development of one side of the body
details:
noun
- superior development of one side of the body
= synonyms: laterality
- the power or right to give orders or make decisions
= synonyms: authorization
- the organic phenomenon in which one of a pair of alleles present in a genotype is expressed in the phenotype and the other allele of the pair is not
- the state that exists when one person or group has power over another
= example: the state that exists when one person or group has power over another
= synonyms: control
